[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man charged after Ardingly gas leak crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged with drinking and driving after a car crashed into a house in West Sussex, causing a gas leak and damaging three other vehicles.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
About 20 people were evacuated from their homes after the crash in Ardingly High Street at 23:20 GMT on Friday.
Andrew John Sleat, 42, of Blackfold Road, Crawley was bailed to appear before Crawley magistrates on 10 December.
Sussex Police said the road was closed for nearly three hours.
